==English==
===Pronunciation===
*(''[[RP]]''): /ˈrəʊtɪk/, /<tt>"r@UtIk</tt>/
*(''US''): rōt'ĭk, /ˈroʊtɪk/, /<tt>"roUtIk</tt>/

===Etymology===
[[Back-formation]] from '''[[rhotacism]]'''

===Adjective===
'''rhotic'''

#Of an English accent, pronouncing the letter ''r'' wherever it appears, as in ''bar'' ([[w:IPA|IPA]] /bɑːr/) and ''bard'' or ''barred'' (IPA /bɑːrd/); this trait is common in most of the United States; many parts of the north of England; Scotland; and India.

====Antonyms====
*[[non-rhotic]]

